title: 2022 United States Senate elections
added: There will be two ballot items for the same seat: a general election, to fill the [[Classes of United States Senators|Class 3 seat]] beginning with the [[118th United States Congress]] beginning on January 3, 2023, and a special election, to fill that seat for the final weeks of the [[117th United States Congress|117th Congress]]. Democrat [[Alex Padilla]] was appointed to fill the vacancy created by [[Kamala Harris]]'s election to the vice presidency, and he is seeking a full term.<ref>https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/574242-california-rule-change-means-padilla-faces-extra-election</ref>

title: 2022 United States Senate elections
added: Evan McMullin, political activist, former CIA operations officer, and 2016 presidential candidate has declared he will run for Senator Lee's seat in the 2022 election.
